# Shayn MIS Frontend — Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Pages: src/pages/{feature}/page.tsx (named export)
- API layer: src/services/{feature}/{feature}.api.ts
- Mutations: src/services/{feature}/{feature}.query.ts (React Query)
- State: src/store/slices/{feature}Slice.ts (Redux Toolkit)
- Shared UI: src/components/shared/ | Layout: src/components/layout/

## TypeScript
- verbatimModuleSyntax: true — type-only imports MUST use `import type`
- strict: true, noUnusedLocals: true, noUnusedParameters: true
- Named exports only — no default exports (except Redux reducers)
- Path aliases: @/, @components/*, @pages/*, @store/*, @services/*, @utils/*, @lib/*, @app/types/*

## State Management
- ALL fetched data and UI state → Redux (useAppSelector / useAppDispatch)
- Mutations only → React Query (useMutation)
- No useState for fetched data, filters, pagination, dialogs

## API
- baseService: Axios instance in src/services/configs/baseService.ts
- apiService: auto-unwraps response.data.data in src/services/configs/apiService.ts
- Always use API_ENDPOINTS from src/utils/constants/api.constant.ts
- Always PUT for updates — never PATCH

## Forms
- Zod schemas: src/utils/validations/index.ts only — never in component files
- React Hook Form + zodResolver

## Quality
- 0 ESLint warnings (--max-warnings 0)
- logger from src/lib/logger.ts — never console.log
- cn() from src/lib/utils.ts for all conditional Tailwind
- Toast on every mutation success and error
